Pre-Game Insights: Iqraam Rayners aims to score one or two goals in the international friendly for Bafana Bafana against Algeria in Algiers.
Coach Hugo Broos has confirmed that Iqraam Rayners will start against Algeria at the 40,000-seat Stade Nelson Mandela.
Rayners' performance in the DStv Premiership has been integral to Stellenbosch FC's strong 2023-2024 campaign.
Rayners is auditioning for a place in the Bafana squad for June’s World Cup qualifiers against Nigeria and Zimbabwe.
Khanyisa Mayo, another local-based striker, has found the step up to Bafana challenging.
Orlando Pirates’ Evidence Makgopa, who is injured, has managed to make an impression under coach Hugo Broos.
Rayners will have a stronger combination around him than the experimental XI fielded against Andorra.
Algeria, who recently beat Bolivia 3-2, are looking to win back public support and impress their new coach Vladimir Petković.
